environment：
pietty

command：
F74012099@C-2012-2:~/project1$ make
make: `main' is up to date.
F74012099@C-2012-2:~/project1$ ./main

requirement:
1. Develop an nondeterministic and interactive game.
2. Include at least two classes (in separate files).
3. Draw UML class diagram in your report.
4. Write a Makefile to compile your program.
5. Display time (in seconds) on screen.
6. At least 3 levels of difficulty.
7. Output the map when the game is over.
8. Simply move the cursor on screen. DO NOT repaint your screen!!!

How to Play?
• Uncover a mine, and the game ends.
• Uncover an empty square, and you keep playing.
• Uncover a number, and it tells you how many mines lay hidden in the eight surrounding squares
—information you use to deduce which nearby squares are safe to click.

ncurses
• ncurses is a programming library providing an API, allowing the programmer to write text user interfaces in a terminal-independent manner.
• In cygwin, remember to install package Libs->libncurses-devel

